  "notes_relevant": [
    {
      "layer": "root",
      "id": 923,
      "title": "Select Options",
      "text_preview": "Select the options in the black switch node according to the following workflow table:\n\n\nWorkflow:                             |Select options:\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nText to Video                         |01 Text to Video\nText + Audio to Video                 |01 Text to Video + Audio input\n                                      |\nImage to Video                        |02 Image to Video\nImage + Audio to Video                |02 Image to Video + Audio input\n                                      |\nFirst/Last Frame to Video             |02 Image to Video + Last Frame input\nFirst/Last Frame + Audio to Video     |02 Image to Video + Last Frame input + Audio input\n                                      |\nFirst/Mid/Last Frame to Video         |02 Image to Video + Last + Mid Frame input\nFirst/Mid/Last Frame + Audio to Video |02 Image to Video + Last + Mid Frame input + Audio input\n                                      |\nVideo to Video                        |03 Video to Video (this option extends your start video)\n\n\nAttention:\nMake sure you select the right switches according to the above table only (otherwise you might get error messages). According to your selection all necessary inputs are highlighted automatically in subgroup \"P\".\n\n\n"
    },
    {
      "layer": "root",
      "id": 280,
      "title": "How to use this workflow",
      "text_preview": "Preperation:\n\n1. Download all models and save them at the specified directories.\n2. Select/check in every blue model loader node your downloaded models.\n   (Please check this twice, a lot of reported issues are caused by model mismatch). \n\n\nRun:\n1. Go to group \"Input\" and select your options in the black switch node (use the Select Option table to find the \n   right options).\n2. Set your values in the brown input nodes: \"Clip Length\", \"Longer Edge\" and \"Aspect Ratio\"\n   set optional values like \"Seed\", etc.,\n   make all inputs in the highlighted (not muted) yellow subgroup \"P\" (brown input nodes and green loader nodes).\n3. Enter your prompts.\n4. Choose/select optional Loras.\n5. Click start."
    },
    {
      "layer": "root",
      "id": 937,
      "title": "Attention: Group Name \"P\" and Node Titel Tags",
      "text_preview": "Attention:\nGroup name and node titel tags are essential for automatic switching between options! \n\nDon`t edit group name \"P\".\nDon`t edit node titel tags like: [[P:02 Image to Video]] for example."
    },
    {
      "layer": "root",
      "id": 284,
      "title": "Model Links",
      "text_preview": "**Workflow Page:** [Workflow](https://civitai.com/models/2354193/ltx-2-all-in-one-workflow-textimagevideoaudio-to-video-running-on-rtx-3060-with-12-gb-vram-32-gb-ram?modelVersionId=2647783\n)\n\n\n**Diffusion Model**       \n- [ltx-2.3-22b-dev-Q6_K.gguf](https://huggingface.co/vantagewithai/LTX-2.3-GGUF/blob/main/dev/ltx-2.3-22b-dev-Q6_K.gguf)\n\n**Text Encoder**\n- [gemma_3_12B_it_fp4_mixed.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/ltx-2/blob/main/split_files/text_encoders/gemma_3_12B_it_fp4_mixed.safetensors)\n\n\n**Dual Clip Connector**\n- [ltx-2.3_text_projection_bf16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/LTX2.3_comfy/blob/main/text_encoders/ltx-2.3_text_projection_bf16.safetensors)\n\n**Audio VAE**\n- [LTX23_audio_vae_bf16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/LTX2.3_comfy/blob/main/vae/LTX23_audio_vae_bf16.safetensors)\n\n**Video VAE**   \n- [LTX23_video_vae_bf16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/LTX2.3_comfy/blob/main/vae/LTX23_video_vae_bf16.safetensors)\n\n**Spatial Upscaler**   \n- [ltx-2.3-spatial-upscaler-x2-1.1.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Lightricks/LTX-2.3/tree/main)\n\n**Tiny VAE for previews**   \n- [taeltx2_3.safetensors](https://github.com/madebyollin/taehv/blob/main/safetensors/taeltx2_3.safetensors)\n\n**Destilled Lora**   \n- [ltx-2.3-22b-distilled-lora-dynamic_fro09_avg_rank_105_bf16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/LTX2.3_comfy/tree/main/loras)\n\n\n\n\n\nFile save location\n\n```\nComfyUI/\n├───📂 models/\n│   ├───📂 diffusion_models/\n│   │   └─── ltx"
    },
    {
      "layer": "root",
      "id": 413,
      "title": "Input Help Subgroup \"P\"",
      "text_preview": "T2V: No further inputs needed.\n\nI2V: Load your First Frame image and optional your Mid/Last Frame images. All images get automatically resized and cropped.\n\nV2V: This option extends your input video by taking the \"style\" of the given video.\n     Load your video and set \"Clip Length\" = your start video length + desired extension length.\n     Create your prompt like this:\n     <very short description of your input video> + \"the video continious with\" + \"full description how it schould go on\".\n     Your input video get automatically resized and cropped.\n\nAudio input: Load your audio file and set clip length according to your Audio length."
    },
    {
      "layer": "root",
      "id": 279,
      "title": "All-In-One LTX-2.3 Workflow, runs perfect with RTX 3060 GPU with 12 GB VRAM",
      "text_preview": "Simple to use all-In-One LTX-2 workflow with options for Text/Image/FLF/Video/Audio to Video.\n\nRequirements:\n- GPU with 12 GB VRAM (some users reported it runs with 8 GB too)\n- 32 GB VRAM\n- Swap file size: 64 - 128 GB\n\n\nRuns very fast: 5 second (1280 x 864) Video: < 10 minutes.\nGeneration of long high quality videos in one run possible: 10 - 20 seconds without any issues,\n\nBrilliant audio generation (speech/sound) with LTX-2.\n\nSimple to use workflow:\n- easy switching between all options with Orchestrator Node Muter,\n- all steps highly automated: no manual frame or aspect ratio calculations necessary,\n- easy to set inputs by predefined sliders (no risk to set wrong inputs, like wrong aspect ratios or wrong frame \n  counts).\n\nThis workflow ensures strict compliance with the LTX-2.3 specifications:\n- aspect ratios of 16:9/9:16,\n- Width and Hight divisible by 32.\n\n\nImportant:\nThis workflow is intended for advanced comfyui users who know how to install and operate the system and are able to resolve basic system errors themselves, like as node conflicts, or general system issues."
    },
    {
      "layer": "New Subgraph",
